<h2>Our favorite ways to use this dip</h2>
<p>The options are truly endless with this red pepper dip. Here are some ideas to get you started:</p>
<ul>
<li>As a dip for <a href="https://amzlink.to/az0xcTH7Z8MqB" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener sponsored">pita chips</a>, <a title="Spicy Ranch Baked Crackers" href="https://www.ambitiouskitchen.com/ranch-crackers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">crackers</a>, <a href="https://amzlink.to/az0AYzelfMlvS" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener sponsored">pretzels</a>, or fresh veggies</li>
<li>Spread onto a veggie-packed sandwich or in a wrap like these <a title="Herby Chicken Meatball Pitas with Jalapeño Tzatziki" href="https://www.ambitiouskitchen.com/herby-chicken-meatball-pitas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Herby Chicken Meatball Pitas</a></li>
<li>On top of a crusty piece of sourdough, or even with your favorite grilled proteins</li>
</ul>
